<br>
&quot;This'll be easy, just a big hitting paralope&quot;. My thoughts where based on no true experience with aggro creatures or Endor. It was time to start learning.<br>
<br>
I ran a few missions with friends, learnt my way around both the outposts, died a lot at the start and saw a few adults critters I wanted. It was time to hook into the baby hunting. <br>
<br>
The first jaunt was a run from the Smuggler outpost to the Research outpost checking everything out. I run from everything, put my weapon away, stop/wait for my radar to catch up with the mobs when spotting lairs and use maskscent breaking as a good early warning device. Arachne mobs all over the place and not a lot or Merek/Boar Wolf action. Spotted a baby Bloodseeker mite. My first target for the day. The slow walk in worked and maskscent held it was a good start. I was half way across a river with the critter under me. /tame and BANG, first go got myself a Bloodmite. Well this is a piece of cake. Time to keep going.<br>
<br>
4km from the research outpost I spot a heap of Boar Pigs. Sneaking around a stretched group of 5 I spot a baby Boar Pig, not exactly what I wanted but it's a start. Sneak in, sucess. Maskscent, sucess. /Tame, fail,fail,fail, he gets the shits up. I ran straight out and got no extra attention and he just left me alone in the end. Time to head back in. Only one more fail and I got me a pigdog. &quot;Well this is all going good&quot;.<br>
<br>
Another 2km along I find a group of 10-12 Boar Wolves spread out alone a ridge. &quot;There&quot; got a Boar Wolf Ravanger Baby in my sights. This is all going great. Sneak in, sucess. Maskscent, sucess. /Tame, fail,fail,fail,fail,fail,fail,fail,fail  . . . come one what's going on here. BANG I made him mad . . . it went from bad to worse in a big way. 4 adults were on quicker than you could say &quot;Big Baldy Badger&quot;. I was dead even faster with the suckers running faster than burst run.<br>
<br>
This is not going to stop me. The next 4 days where spent running around, looking, dieing, loosing hope. Running out from the outpost in all directions I found them to the NE and SW of the base all the time. Then just before the servers went down I spotted him (5 min to server drop). A group of 3, Adult ravager, adult boar wolf and a baby ravager. This is it.<br>
<br>
Snuck in and got into taming range. First try BANG, he was into me for failing to tame. Ran off without burst run and bubby was the only one on my heels hitting for 10-30. Once he broke off the attack I was straight back in once maskscent was up. He wandered all the way back to the group so another tricky one. All went well until he got upset with me failing the tame. This time the Boar Wolf adult came with him. I layed there flat on my back after a very brief run staring at the stars praying the server didn't drop. <br>
<br>
Back in, 100 health, no time to heal up. While I snuck back in I slipped into a run and sprinted right up to him. Maskscent held and I was cursing my hotkeys. /Tame, BANG, I now have a Boar Wolf Ravager. Check the clock and was 30secs past the predicted server drop. <br>
<br>
Now for the Bloodstained Merek challenge tommorow.<br>
<br>
Bellor<br>
