I walk within 25-30m with maskscent on, go prone and just hit numlock and let myself crawl the rest of the way.  I get within 9m and hit Tame, it failed.  I try it again, it failed.  Again, failed.  I failed to catch a plain boar wolf baby about 7 times.  But, after putting in this much work, I'm not about to just crawl back away and leave.  As I'm right in the middle of about my eigth try I notice on my radar that about 4 green dots are moving towards me, it's my putz groupmates.  I shout &quot;IM TRYING TO TAME THIS, GET AWAY,&quot; they're still coming...  So I shout &quot;STOP GO BACK!&quot;  Nothing.  They get right up to about 8m behind me with no maskscent on, no camo, not prone, heck, not even walking up.  So of course the whole pack goes aggro.  I jump up and start running for the camp shooting suppressionfire the whole way there trying to give myself some distance till my friends can jump in and help my kill it (and hopefully send their creatures to distract it).  But instead, since I'm a carbineer, I miss about 6 times and my shot that does hit Fails to Change the Targets Posture.<br>
In the end it killed me, and only me.  Then they walked back to where they were and left the others alone.  What a great experience!  After that I left the group and headed back to Naboo.<br>
<br>
But I didn't know CHs with 2,2,0,0 could catch any mereks; I'll see you on Endor. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bellor>Bellor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.webone.com.au/~bellor/Graphics/dancing.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#70DB93>(9/10/03 6:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://webone.com.au/~bellor/Graphics/minibellmini.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Finding my first pet after 2/2/0/0</span><hr size=1> Boodstained and Assasins . . . I tried a few but failed (and died) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cobragt18>cobragt18</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://img1.ranchoweb.com/images/cobragt18/pirate-swordclear.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#70DB93>(9/11/03 6:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://img2.ranchoweb.com/images/cobragt18/pirate-knifeteeth-new.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Finding my first pet after 2/2/0/0</span><hr size=1> I just landed on Endor again yesterday looking for a merek and arachne, dropped two falumpasets to make room.  I started wandering west from the smugglers outpost as that is the direction I usually find crowded with every type of creature and NPC imaginable on Endor.  Didn't find much so I started heading south, and there it was, a glorious bloodstained merek (baby), how lucky a find it was (probably the first baby one I had ever seen in my many, many trips to Endor).<br>
I started +shift walking towards it, masked my scent, and went prone about 30m out.  As I crawled towards it a creature noticed me and I had to sit tight about 17m away until I could remask.  I get my /maskscent back and move in for the /tame.  Once within 9m I attempt it, but it's not even before I can get to &quot;Good...err....boy?&quot; before it scampers away to the comfort of an adult, leaving me laying there out of range.  So I'm now forced to crawl closer and within easy reach of what is now 3 or 4 other mereks.  I /tame it again 2 or 3 times with no luck, then, with no reason (except maybe the 2 other guys about 20-25m away fighting something else), something detects me and I'm again left sitting there with no camouflage.  So I now lay there prone (in every sense of the word) and it's about 3 seconds before one of them aggros me and about .5 seconds after that that they kill me before I can even get to my feet and to /burstrun out of there.<br>
So now I'm wandering around Endor looking for another (with little luck).  At times I've found myself walking through the woods without spotting a single creature for about a half hour; ridiculous.  So maybe if you've been able to find a couple you could share any particularly good spots or areas.  I know I usually find mereks in the mountainous region around the Smuggler post, especially West and North but these spots seem to be dry.  So I'm still out there looking and refuse to leave till I find one.<br>
<br>
Anyway, good luck with your search, hope it goes better than mine. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bellor>Bellor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.webone.com.au/~bellor/Graphics/dancing.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#70DB93>(9/17/03 6:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://webone.com.au/~bellor/Graphics/minibellmini.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Finding my first pet after 2/2/0/0</span><hr size=1> I find them around either outpost. I do most of my hunting from the research outpost and heading east avoids the Marauders. Found a Baby assasin today. DNA sampled the only adult nearby and got the assasin on the second attempt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cobragt18>cobragt18</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://img1.ranchoweb.com/images/cobragt18/pirate-swordclear.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#70DB93>(9/22/03 6:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://img2.ranchoweb.com/images/cobragt18/pirate-knifeteeth-new.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Finding my first pet after 2/2/0/0</span><hr size=1> I've caught a Hanadak Drifter and a Mantrigue Night Stalker so far.  The Drifter appeared right after my friends and I blew up the lair (just popped out and since the lair was gone and not being attacked he didn't aggro).  One of my friend tried to catch him twice but failed and let me give it a try since he had so many better pets than I anyway.  I caught him in 3 tries and he, luckily, never aggrod me.<br>
<br>
I found the Mantrigue in amongst some adults and had to crawl in to get a chance.  Tried about 7 times to catch him, finally succeeded after about 4-5 aggros and running away and 2 deaths.<br>
<br>
Still looking for the elusive merek and starting to wonder if arachnes even spawn babies anymore. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm14.showPrevMessage?topicID=3.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm14.showNextMessage?topicID=3.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm14.emailToFriend?topicID=3.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm14.threadControl?topicID=3.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm14.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm14.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub60.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post>